<title>FRANCE: France mulls euro keyring calculator.</title>
<headline>France mulls euro keyring calculator.</headline>
<dateline>PARIS 1996-10-30</dateline>
<text>
<p>France is considering issuing a keyring calculator which will convert francs to euros to avoid headaches when the single European currency comes into effect in 1999, government spokesman Alain Lamassoure said on Wednesday.</p>
<p>Lamassoure said President Jacques Chirac suggested in a cabinet meeting that experts should look into making a small calculator, perhaps a keyring, that would allow people to easily convert francs into euros and back by pushing two or three buttons.</p>
<p>He said the calculator should be &quot;user-friendly, strong, easy to read for the short-sighted and widely available to the population&quot;.</p>
</text>
